The paper deals with crowdsourcing and machine learning, which are both relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The specific tasks of delineating cells in microscopy images and analyzing sentiment in tweets suggest computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) as potential sub-categories. Finally, the use of machine learning to predict optimal worker allocation falls under the umbrella of machine learning (cs.LG).
